# Changelog

## 1.2.0 (2026-04-07)
- Rewrite queue storage to indexed keys (q_0…q_199) — each background cycle loads only
  BATCH_SIZE readings regardless of total queue size, eliminating background heap crashes
- Queue now safely handles 200 readings (~16h buffer) with no memory pressure
- Automatic migration: old array-based queue (pending_readings) cleared on first run
- Readings stored as 3 fields (ts, bat, charging); device metadata merged at sync time
- Batched sync: 30 readings per POST cycle, drains large queues over successive cycles

